abstract: From depictions of a far-left conspiracy to attacks on freshman legislators, the escalating messaging provides a preview of the political advertising to come.
snippet: From depictions of a far-left conspiracy to attacks on freshman legislators, the escalating messaging provides a preview of the political advertising to come.
lead_paragraph: Two minutes after Speaker Nancy Pelosi had announced an official impeachment inquiry, the Trump campaign placed a new ad on Facebook, dropping $12,000 on an “Impeachment Poll” for its supporters.

abstract: East Harlem residents welcome a plan to extend the Second Avenue Subway, but they’re worried it might change the neighborhood.
snippet: East Harlem residents welcome a plan to extend the Second Avenue Subway, but they’re worried it might change the neighborhood.
lead_paragraph: Maribel Burgos barely has time to change into her uniform before she has to clock in at the McDonald’s in Lower Manhattan where she works, even though she gives herself 90 minutes to commute from her home in East Harlem.

abstract: As officials tried to piece together clues from Belgium, Britain, Bulgaria, China and Ireland, a Vietnamese woman’s relatives said they feared she might be among the dead.
snippet: As officials tried to piece together clues from Belgium, Britain, Bulgaria, China and Ireland, a Vietnamese woman’s relatives said they feared she might be among the dead.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Two more men and a woman were arrested on suspicion of conspiracy to traffic people and manslaughter after 39 people were found dead in a refrigerated trailer in southeastern England, the British police said on Friday, the first indication from officials that the deaths were linked to human smuggling.

headline_main: G.O.P. Protest at Impeachment Inquiry: ‘Thuggish and Juvenile’

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg began his campaign in obscurity, staking out progressive positions. As his standing rises, he has moved toward the center, hoping to draw support away from Joe Biden.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg began his campaign in obscurity, staking out progressive positions. As his standing rises, he has moved toward the center, hoping to draw support away from Joe Biden.
lead_paragraph: PHILADELPHIA — In February, Pete Buttigieg, then a virtually unknown presidential candidate, praised the Green New Deal as “the right beginning.” In June he called for decriminalizing illegal border crossings. A month later he dismissed criticisms of raising middle class taxes to pay for expanded health care, calling it “a distinction without a difference.”

abstract: House Democrats, once eyeing an impeachment vote by Thanksgiving, now conceded they may have to go slower as they plan public hearings to drive home their case.
snippet: House Democrats, once eyeing an impeachment vote by Thanksgiving, now conceded they may have to go slower as they plan public hearings to drive home their case.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats have resigned themselves to the likelihood that impeachment proceedings against President Trump will extend into the Christmas season, as they plan a series of public hearings intended to make the simplest and most devastating possible public case in favor of removing Mr. Trump.

abstract: He knew Democrats would criticize him. When Republicans started doing so, he changed his mind.
snippet: He knew Democrats would criticize him. When Republicans started doing so, he changed his mind.
lead_paragraph: He knew he was inviting criticism by choosing his own luxury golf club in Miami for the site of a gathering of world leaders at the Group of 7 summit in June, President Trump told his aides opposed to the choice, and he was prepared for the inevitable attack from Democrats.

abstract: Here’s a rundown of major things that happened in the presidential campaign this week.
snippet: Here’s a rundown of major things that happened in the presidential campaign this week.
lead_paragraph: We here on The New York Times Politics desk had a busy and exciting week helping to host the fourth Democratic debate. Tuesday night was especially frenetic, with the debate, third-quarter fund-raising reports and a pair of major endorsements all in the news.

abstract: Are the wealthy addicted to money, competition, or just feeling important? Yes.
snippet: Are the wealthy addicted to money, competition, or just feeling important? Yes.
lead_paragraph: “Billionaires should not exist,” Senator Bernie Sanders said last month. And, at the Democratic presidential debate this week, he said that the wealth disparity in America is “a moral and economic outrage.”

abstract: Britain’s prime minister cited a “great new deal that takes back control,” hours after a Northern Irish party rejected the agreement.
snippet: Britain’s prime minister cited a “great new deal that takes back control,” hours after a Northern Irish party rejected the agreement.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — Britain and the European Union agreed on a Brexit deal Thursday, setting the stage for a fateful showdown in the British Parliament, where Prime Minister Boris Johnson faces an uphill struggle to marshal enough votes for his plan after three years of anguished, politically corrosive debate.
